Summaries

Five sample summaries

[1] First, he explained what short-termism is, which is widespread in various parts of society. Short-termism means looking at things only in the short term. For example, in the U.S., one high school student drops out of school every 26 seconds because of short-termism. It makes it impossible for teachers to support each student individually. He criticized modern people who are unable to think long-termism and try to solve problems only with quick fixes. After that he explained that there are three ways to plan for the long term. They are transgenerational thinking, future thinking, and telos thinking. He said that based on the technology that has developed since modern times, we only view things through a technology-centered filter. It means that we always think it can be solved through technology or not. Also, he argued that we are in control of our future and that we can change through the process of thinking it through.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       
[2] We increasingly make decisions based on short-term goals. Then, the speaker suggests to stop short-termism in order to solve big problems. In fact, short-termism has caused a lot of problems in the world. For example, more students dropout of school, or infrastructure is not improved. This short-termism was influenced by scientific and technological developments or advances. He calls technological fixes sandbag strategies. Of course, it is effective, but it is temporary and it will not change the world or solve any major problems. Therefore, he insists that a long path must be used and the three ways to plan for the very long term. They are transgenerational thinking, futures thinking, and telos thinking. Also, he adds that we should quit looking at things through the dominant technological lens. Conclusively, with this process, with this thinking, we can make a difference.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      
[3] His job is to predict the future. There are various problems currently occurring, but in order to solve them we must overcome short termism. There are many things we can't do because of short termism. Furthermore, if a company is short termism, there is a risk that safety will be threatened. To combat short termism, he invented the longpath. There are three ways of thinking about longpath. The first is transgenerational thinking. This is an ethical perspective that is shared across generations and allows us to expand our role in problem-solving. The second is future thinking. When we think about problems, we often focus on technology. This is not a mistake, but it is not fundamentally thought out. Thinking about various futures is the first step to solving problems. The third is telos thinking. This idea originated in Greece and refers to an ultimate goal or purpose. Although the word "future" is often thought of as a noun, it is actually a verb. Nothing will happen in the future unless you take action. We should think more about the future.                                                                                                                                                           
[4] > People in this modern world are invaded with a mental state so-called short-termism. The speaker developed a practice named LONGPATH to overcome the issues caused by short-termism. It is a practice that people revisit different ways of thinking in making a decision, and there are three key ways of thinking as follows: transgenerational thinking, futures thinking, and Teros thinking. With transgenerational thinking, people can think about social issues such as education and inequality in a longer span; in addition, this can be practiced on a very personal level such as eating out with family members. He then, pointed out that people today only look at the future through the lens of technology, ending up thinking about the future in one way. With futures thinking, we can open up ourselves to various futures inspired by faith, art, science, etc. Finally, he suggested that people today do not think about the world after they do something, and that is why they cannot get out of a hamster wheel. With Teros Thinking, people can act for the future while knowing what comes after they do things. In his opinion, future should be a verb, and people can take action and make a change for the future. <
[5] Ari Wallach points out that a lot of people today think too much about the future in short termism. Short termism has caused serious problems, such as the Gulf of Mexico oil spill, which occurred because the CEO failed to spend enough money on safety equipment. He recommends long term thinking instead of short term thinking. There are three types of long term thinking: Transgenerational thinking, Future thinking, and Telos thinking. Transgenerational thinking is a kind of ethics that is shared across generations and passed down from parents to children. Future thinking is a way of thinking about the future that corresponds to each era. He argues that modern people think too much about technology, but we shouldnt rely on it too much. Finally, Telos thinking is thinking about To what end?. Through all of these ideas, he argues that it is important to look at the future from various angles and over the long term.

I'm about to start job hunting, so I'd like to use this video as a reference to think carefully about my future.
